Riddle:

An collision involving two automobiles occurred in the town center. A man driving a small green automobile had passed a large black car. The driver had underestimated the space between himself and oncoming traffic and had to service back in, forcing the black car to serve and crash into a shop window. When the passengers of the automobiles were investigated, everyone in the green car was fine, but there was one dead guy in the black car. Why, though, was the driver of the green automobile not charged with manslaughter?

Possible Answers:

    A. The black car was an autonomous vehicle and had no living driver or passengers
    B. The black car was a hears and was on its way to a funeral.
    C. The police thought the traffic accident is not serious enough to fine the man.
    D. None of above.

